/PG510/XX/PR

Dear God, protect my tongue from evil,/PR

and my lips from telling lies./PR

And toward my adversaries may my spirit remain tranquil,/PR

may I always remain ready for the needs of others./PR

Open my heart toward your Torah,/PR

let my spirit seek to do all that you ask of me./PR

Let all who bear me animosity/PR

be brought to reconsider their ill-will./PR

Act for the sake of your name./PR

Act for the sake of your deeds./PR

Act for the sake of your holiness./PR

Act for the sake of your Torah./PR

So that all those dear to you may find release,/PR

let your right hand bring deliverance, and answer me./PR

May my words of prayer/PR

and my heartòs meditation be seen favorably,/PR

/SCP/XXRECIOUS /XXO/XXNE/XX, my rock, my champion./PR

May the one who creates harmony above/PR

make peace for us and for all Israel,/PR

and for all who dwell on earth./PR

And say: Amen./PR

/PR

Your righteousness endures, forever just,/PR

your Torah, true eternally./PR

Your justice reaches to the highest heavens,/PR

which you, through your great deeds, have made./PR

Who is like you, God?/PR

Your justness like the mighty mountain crests,/PR

your judgments like the greatest ocean depths./PR

To human being and beast alike/PR

